        "references": [
            "We also conduct statistical tests of significance using paired t-test to assess whether the improvement in performance achieved by FedAR is statistically significant. We compare the test accuracy of FedAR against each of the baselines individually for both CIFAR-10 and SVHN, and for pm​i​n=0.1subscript𝑝𝑚𝑖𝑛0.1p_{min}=0.1 and pm​i​n=0.5subscript𝑝𝑚𝑖𝑛0.5p_{min}=0.5. The results are illustrated in Table 2; each entry\nin the table denotes the p-value of the paired t-test between FedAR and the corresponding baseline (denoted in the columns) for the corresponding dataset (denoted in the rows). From the table, we find that the improvement in performance achieved by FedAR is statistically significant (p<0.001𝑝0.001p<0.001) compared to all the baselines, consistently for both the datasets and both values of pm​i​nsubscript𝑝𝑚𝑖𝑛p_{min}. These results further corroborate the promise and potential of FedAR.\nFedAR also shows superior performance on the MNIST dataset with lower training losses and higher test accuracy upon convergence, as elaborated in the Appendix."
